      vulnType: Network Security
      description: >-
        <p>Egress filtering is used to restrict and monitor outbound traffic
        from one network to another. During the internal assessment, the
        consultants discovered it was able to make arbitrary connections to
        hosts on the Internet. This showed a lack of egress filtering in place
        on <<full_company_name>>'s network.  An adversary can leverage  this
        lack of egress filtering to exfiltrate data from the network.</p>
      observation: <p></p>
      remediation: >-
        <p>It is recommended that <<full_company_name>> implement an egress
        policy. The policy should deny all traffic by default and only allow
        approved traffic.  Only traffic necessary for business reasons should be
        allow out while all other traffic is denied.</p>
